      therealeffingaeiouy - <br />Ha - my wife fell for that one last week as well, and she is pretty smart.<br /><br />Their twist was the 'pay for it process' up front, rather than at the end.  She thought she was renewing her liscense with the State RMV, and paid.   20 minutes later, after the charge had cleared, they sent her the link to the DMV, and a PDF of the form she has to fill out if she just wants to go in person.  <br /><br />I suspect we can get the $ back after some hassle, but WTF.      I went back and looked at the page she was on, and if you look at the small print, they tell you they are not who you think they are and are merely sending you useful information.  But you really have to look for it.
      
