    <div class="body">
      Nasty.  I think most security savvy people either:<br /><br />1) Never click on a link in an email no matter what<br /><br />or<br /><br />2) Click on links, knowing they're well protected from malicious sites via things like NoScript, Sandboxie, etc.<br /><br />I fall into (2), because look, friends send you links to articles and stuff all the time, but even after clicking on a link, I'd never enter actual credentials, but damn, if it was actually on a Google page, where I already permit scripts, and hadn't logged in already, I might well fall for this. I may just retrench into (1) mode.
      
